(1) `label.normal.formatter` can be used to customize formatter, although it not occurs in doc, which is an omission.

``` javascript
series: [{
    type: 'sankey',
    label: {
        normal: {
            formatter: '{b}'  // {b} is the node.name, or you can use a callback function here.
        }
    }
}]
```

(2) Besides `name`, each `node` in data can be identified by attribute `id`, for eg: 

``` javascript
series: [{
    data: [
        {id: 'source - Romania', name: 'Romania'},
        {id: 'target - Romania', name: 'Romania'},
        ...
    ]
}]
```

